<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">823.30/96a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-25T18:00:00-04:00">August 25, 1930—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>88. The Department appreciates your full and timely reports on recent
                            events in Peru. You are instructed to exert all appropriate efforts to
                            effect the release of Grow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>